# Core conventions

This is a Turborepo with one SvelteKit 2 / Svelte 5 app at `apps/mind-map-sv`.
Always work from the repo root unless a script explicitly says otherwise.

## Architecture: pure logic first, components thin

- Behavior goes into pure TypeScript modules under `apps/mind-map-sv/src/lib/components/<Component>/lib/*.ts` (or a sibling `lib/` for app-level logic).
- Svelte components hold state and wire up pure functions; they should not contain non-trivial branching, math, or data transforms.
- Every pure module has a colocated `*.spec.ts` next to it.
- Example pattern that already exists: `Multigraph/lib/graphMath.ts` ↔ `Multigraph/lib/graphMath.spec.ts`.

## Definition of Done (every change must satisfy these before claiming complete)

1. New behavior has tests. New pure functions get unit specs; new component behavior gets a Storybook story with a `play` function.
2. `pnpm --filter mind-map-sv lint` passes.
3. `pnpm --filter mind-map-sv check` (svelte-check) passes.
4. `pnpm --filter mind-map-sv test:unit -- --run` passes.
5. If you touched gestures, layout, or anything visible: run the relevant story locally (or rely on the storybook Vitest project to run the `play`).
6. Commit message follows Conventional Commits (see `commits.mdc`).
7. No tracked changes to `.svelte-kit/`, build output, or log files (those are gitignored).

You must actually run the commands above and report results. Do not claim done from "I think this is fine".

## When in doubt

- Prefer adding a pure function with a spec over inlining logic in a `.svelte` file.
- Prefer adding a story over inventing a new test harness.
- Prefer extending the existing `StageHarness.svelte` pattern over adding component-level Vitest tests.
- Read `docs/roadmaps/` for the active roadmap and current milestone before starting non-trivial work.

## Roadmaps, milestones, plans

Three layers, each smaller in scope:

- **Roadmap** — the big picture. One per release/era.
- **Milestone** — *what* and *why* a piece of the roadmap delivers, plus
  acceptance criteria and open questions.
- **Plan** — *how* to deliver a milestone: tasks (one PR each),
  parallelization waves, and per-task agent recommendations.

If a milestone doesn't have a current plan, write one before coding.
Format and authoring checklist live in `.cursor/rules/plans.mdc` and
`docs/roadmaps/PLAN_TEMPLATE.md`.

## Where things live

| Concern | Location |
|---|---|
| Pure graph/layout/physics logic | `apps/mind-map-sv/src/lib/components/ui/Multigraph/lib/*.ts` |
| Component | `apps/mind-map-sv/src/lib/components/ui/<Name>/<Name>.svelte` |
| Story | `apps/mind-map-sv/src/lib/components/ui/<Name>/<Name>.stories.svelte` |
| Unit spec | colocated next to the `.ts` file as `*.spec.ts` |
| E2E | `apps/mind-map-sv/e2e/*.test.ts` |
| Test fixtures | `apps/mind-map-sv/src/lib/components/ui/Multigraph/lib/testFixtures.ts` |
| Roadmaps & plans | `docs/roadmaps/<YYYY-MM-DD> <name>/` |
| Plan template | `docs/roadmaps/PLAN_TEMPLATE.md` |
